17
00:02:16,136 --> 00:02:18,180
[NEWSCASTER 39A] Welcome back
to our Summer Special.

18
00:02:18,221 --> 00:02:20,140
"All Might: The Journey
from Number One Hero

19
00:02:20,182 --> 00:02:21,850
to UA High School Teacher."

20
00:02:21,892 --> 00:02:24,269
Today, we'll be looking back
on All Might's achievements,

21
00:02:24,311 --> 00:02:25,854
and his incredible rise to f‐‐

22
00:02:33,528 --> 00:02:35,697
[SHIGARAKI]
I've figured it out.

23
00:02:35,739 --> 00:02:38,825
Why the Hero Killer
pisses me off so much.

24
00:02:38,867 --> 00:02:42,245
And why those UA brats
drive me crazy.

25
00:02:42,287 --> 00:02:43,955
It's because of All Might.

26
00:02:43,997 --> 00:02:45,666
And that stupid grin,

27
00:02:45,707 --> 00:02:48,001
as though he doesn't
have a care in the world.

28
00:02:48,043 --> 00:02:50,045
Smiling thoughtlessly.

29
00:02:50,087 --> 00:02:52,464
As if there's no one
he can't save.

30
00:02:52,506 --> 00:02:54,883
Like he's undefeatable.

31
00:02:59,554 --> 00:03:01,723
[KUROGIRI]
Izuku Midoriya.

32
00:03:01,765 --> 00:03:03,975
Quirkless until middle school,

33
00:03:04,017 --> 00:03:06,645
when he suddenly
manifested a power.

34
00:03:06,687 --> 00:03:08,563
After enrolling at UA High,

35
00:03:08,605 --> 00:03:11,316
he distinguished himself by
finishing in the top eight

36
00:03:11,358 --> 00:03:14,653
at their world‐famous
sports festival.

37
00:03:14,695 --> 00:03:16,947
Then, during the Hosu incident,

38
00:03:16,988 --> 00:03:20,367
he and his friends fought
the Hero Killer, Stain...

39
00:03:20,409 --> 00:03:21,785
...and won.

40
00:03:21,827 --> 00:03:22,911
Afterward,

41
00:03:22,953 --> 00:03:27,040
the Hero Killer chose
to spare the child's life.

42
00:03:27,082 --> 00:03:30,293
Izuku Midoriya was
acknowledged by Stain,

43
00:03:30,335 --> 00:03:33,797
the man seeking out
true heroes, as worthy.

44
00:03:33,839 --> 00:03:37,759
He judged Tomura Shigaraki
quite differently.

45
00:03:38,927 --> 00:03:40,721
[SHIGARAKI]
Just picture it.

46
00:03:40,762 --> 00:03:43,807
A world without the
Symbol of Peace.

47
00:03:43,849 --> 00:03:46,309
I'll show society
just how fragile

48
00:03:46,351 --> 00:03:49,229
their sense of safety is.

49
00:03:54,401 --> 00:03:56,069
[IZUKU] Now that our
intense first semester

50
00:03:56,111 --> 00:03:58,363
at UA High is over,
me and my classmates

51
00:03:58,405 --> 00:04:00,824
are out for summer vacation.

52
00:04:00,866 --> 00:04:03,243
But that doesn't mean
we have time to relax.

53
00:04:03,285 --> 00:04:06,079
We've got a training camp
in the woods coming up.

54
00:04:06,121 --> 00:04:08,373
And I want to be as
prepared as possible.

55
00:04:08,415 --> 00:04:10,125
[sighs]

56
00:04:11,334 --> 00:04:12,169
[MAN 1A]
Who is he?

57
00:04:12,210 --> 00:04:14,296
The guy's already saved
100 people at least,

58
00:04:14,337 --> 00:04:16,047
and it hasn't even
been ten minutes.

59
00:04:16,089 --> 00:04:18,300
This is... This is crazy.

60
00:04:18,341 --> 00:04:19,968
I can't believe it!

61
00:04:20,010 --> 00:04:22,137
[ALL MIGHT laughing]

62
00:04:22,179 --> 00:04:24,806
[CAMERAMAN 1A]
Look, he's got more!

63
00:04:24,848 --> 00:04:28,393
Fear not, citizens.
Hope has arrived.

64
00:04:28,435 --> 00:04:30,395
Because I am here.

65
00:04:32,063 --> 00:04:33,899
Thanks, All Might.

66
00:04:35,484 --> 00:04:38,320
[IZUKU] There are times I still
can't believe this is my life.

67
00:04:38,361 --> 00:04:40,280
That the number‐one hero
in the world chose

68
00:04:40,322 --> 00:04:42,949
to pass his Quirk,
One For All, on to me.

69
00:04:42,991 --> 00:04:44,493
[doorbell rings]

70
00:04:46,620 --> 00:04:49,122
[IZUKU]
Mineta. Kaminari. Hey!

71
00:04:49,164 --> 00:04:50,248
Heyo, Midoriya!

72
00:04:50,290 --> 00:04:51,875
Come to the pool with us!

73
00:04:51,917 --> 00:04:52,709
The pool?

74
00:04:52,751 --> 00:04:55,712
Yeah. Some fun before
the training camp.

75
00:04:55,754 --> 00:04:58,089
We'll get in some solid laps.

76
00:04:58,131 --> 00:05:00,258
U‐Uh...

77
00:05:01,718 --> 00:05:02,552
[AIZAWA]
Vlad.

78
00:05:02,594 --> 00:05:05,263
We have to increase each of the
students' Quirks this summer.

79
00:05:05,305 --> 00:05:06,431
Agreed.

80
00:05:06,473 --> 00:05:08,266
Why don't you start
by giving me a rundown

81
00:05:08,308 --> 00:05:10,352
of all of Class A's abilities?

82
00:05:10,393 --> 00:05:11,728
If I must.

83
00:05:13,355 --> 00:05:15,232
[AIZAWA]
Let's start with Yuga Aoyama.

84
00:05:15,273 --> 00:05:17,025
His Quirk is Navel Laser.

85
00:05:17,067 --> 00:05:19,986
It's... basically,
a bellybutton laser.

86
00:05:20,028 --> 00:05:23,031
Then we have
Mina Ashido. Quirk: Acid.

87
00:05:23,073 --> 00:05:26,243
She secretes a corrosive
substance that melts targets.

88
00:05:26,284 --> 00:05:29,204
Tsuyu Asui. Her Quirk is Frog.

89
00:05:29,246 --> 00:05:32,415
And she can do pretty much
everything a frog can.

90
00:05:32,457 --> 00:05:36,044
Tenya Iida is the
class rep. Quirk: Engine.

91
00:05:36,086 --> 00:05:39,339
The engines in his calves
grant him super speed.

92
00:05:39,381 --> 00:05:43,176
There's Ochaco Uraraka.
Her Quirk: Zero Gravity.

93
00:05:43,218 --> 00:05:45,637
She can make anything
she touches weightless.

94
00:05:45,679 --> 00:05:48,890
Mashirao Ojiro. His Quirk
is called "Tail."

95
00:05:48,932 --> 00:05:52,018
He can manipulate his tail
as if it were an arm or leg.

96
00:05:52,060 --> 00:05:55,897
Moving on to Denki Kaminari.
Quirk: Electrification.

97
00:05:55,939 --> 00:05:58,859
He discharges built‐up
electricity from his body.

98
00:05:58,900 --> 00:06:01,570
The spiky‐haired one
is Eijiro Kirishima.

99
00:06:01,611 --> 00:06:03,113
Quirk: Hardening.

100
00:06:03,154 --> 00:06:05,407
He can make his
entire body stone‐like.

101
00:06:05,448 --> 00:06:09,202
Koji Koda is the quiet type.
Though, his Quirk is Anivoice.

102
00:06:09,244 --> 00:06:11,162
He uses it to control
animals and insects,

103
00:06:11,204 --> 00:06:13,039
but it can't affect humans.

104
00:06:13,081 --> 00:06:16,543
Rikido Sato is strong.
Quirk: Sugar Rush.

105
00:06:16,585 --> 00:06:20,046
He turns the sugar stored
in his body into pure power.

106
00:06:20,088 --> 00:06:23,508
Then we have Mezo Shoji.
His Quirk is Dupli‐Arms.

107
00:06:23,550 --> 00:06:24,926
He can make other
body parts appear

108
00:06:24,968 --> 00:06:27,220
on the tips of his tentacles.

109
00:06:27,262 --> 00:06:28,305
Kyoka Jiro.

110
00:06:28,346 --> 00:06:30,390
Her Quirk is called
"Earphone Jack."

111
00:06:30,432 --> 00:06:32,517
Using the retractable
plugs on her earlobes,

112
00:06:32,559 --> 00:06:35,103
she can distinguish between
even the quietest of sounds.

113
00:06:35,145 --> 00:06:36,897
Plus, she can use the
speakers on her legs

114
00:06:36,938 --> 00:06:40,233
to release incredibly
devastating sonic bursts.

115
00:06:40,275 --> 00:06:42,652
Hanta Sero has
a Quirk named "Tape."

116
00:06:42,694 --> 00:06:43,945
It has many uses.

117
00:06:43,987 --> 00:06:45,697
He can shoot sticky
tape from his elbows

118
00:06:45,739 --> 00:06:47,282
and use it to apprehend
his opponents,

119
00:06:47,324 --> 00:06:50,368
or simply to swing
around through the air.

120
00:06:50,410 --> 00:06:53,914
Fumikage Tokoyami.
Quirk: Dark Shadow.

121
00:06:53,955 --> 00:06:55,916
He commands a devastating
bird‐like shadow

122
00:06:55,957 --> 00:06:58,293
that gets wilder when
there's no light.

123
00:06:58,335 --> 00:07:00,795
Endeavor's son, Shoto Todoroki.

124
00:07:00,837 --> 00:07:02,672
His Quirk is
Half‐Cold, Half‐Hot.

125
00:07:02,714 --> 00:07:04,466
He can emit ice from the
right side of his body,

126
00:07:04,507 --> 00:07:06,509
and flames from the left.

127
00:07:06,551 --> 00:07:08,970
The Stealth Hero, Toru Hagakure.

128
00:07:09,012 --> 00:07:12,766
Her Quirk: Invisibility.
She's invisible.

129
00:07:12,807 --> 00:07:15,352
The sports festival
winner, Katsuki Bakugo.

130
00:07:15,393 --> 00:07:17,020
Quirk: Explosion.

131
00:07:17,062 --> 00:07:18,939
He sweats a
nitroglycerin‐like substance

132
00:07:18,980 --> 00:07:20,774
and makes it blow up.

133
00:07:20,815 --> 00:07:22,609
Of course, there's
Izuku Midoriya.

134
00:07:22,651 --> 00:07:24,152
His Quirk is Super Power.

135
00:07:24,194 --> 00:07:26,321
He can increase the power
and physical abilities

136
00:07:26,363 --> 00:07:29,658
of isolated appendages,
or his entire body.

137
00:07:29,699 --> 00:07:33,286
[sighs] Minoru Mineta.
His Quirk: Pop Off.

138
00:07:33,328 --> 00:07:35,872
The balls he pulls off his
head can stick to anything,

139
00:07:35,914 --> 00:07:38,458
though he himself
bounces off them.

140
00:07:38,500 --> 00:07:40,669
Finally, there's Momo Yaoyorozu.

141
00:07:40,710 --> 00:07:42,212
Her Quirk is Creation.

142
00:07:42,253 --> 00:07:43,880
She can create
any non‐living thing

143
00:07:43,922 --> 00:07:46,007
from the lipids in her body.

144
00:07:46,049 --> 00:07:47,217
And that's it.

145
00:07:47,258 --> 00:07:50,178
We should also go over
Class B's Quirks‐‐

146
00:07:50,220 --> 00:07:51,680
[MINETA]
Excuse us.

147
00:07:51,721 --> 00:07:53,556
[VLAD]
Yes? What is it?

148
00:07:53,598 --> 00:07:54,891
Sorry to interrupt.

149
00:07:54,933 --> 00:07:56,559
We were wondering about
the form we turned in

150
00:07:56,601 --> 00:07:58,770
a few days ago about the pool.

151
00:07:58,812 --> 00:08:01,398
[AIZAWA] Oh. The school
has granted you permission.

152
00:08:01,439 --> 00:08:03,358
You're allowed to use
the pool until 5 pm.

153
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:04,109
Thanks!

154
00:08:04,150 --> 00:08:06,069
You won't regret this, sir!

155
00:08:06,111 --> 00:08:07,487
You said you wanted
to use the pool

156
00:08:07,529 --> 00:08:09,489
for endurance training, correct?

157
00:08:09,531 --> 00:08:11,032
Make the time count.

158
00:08:11,074 --> 00:08:13,034
[ALL]
Right!

159
00:08:13,076 --> 00:08:15,620
[IZUKU] So, we're using the
pool to improve our stamina.

160
00:08:15,662 --> 00:08:17,372
That's a great idea, Mineta.

161
00:08:17,414 --> 00:08:19,416
Plus, if we're at school,
we can use our Quirks!

162
00:08:19,457 --> 00:08:22,419
It'll be the perfect
way to train!

163
00:08:22,460 --> 00:08:24,504
Just what you'd
expect from us heroes.

164
00:08:24,546 --> 00:08:26,214
You know what we're gonna do.

165
00:08:26,256 --> 00:08:28,258
Go beyond. Plus Ultra!

166
00:08:28,299 --> 00:08:29,843
Ultra!

167
00:08:29,884 --> 00:08:32,053
[KAMINARI] It was a smart
choice to invite Midoriya.

168
00:08:32,095 --> 00:08:33,555
He's a great cover.

169
00:08:33,596 --> 00:08:35,140
[MINETA] If it had just
been us, we wouldn't have

170
00:08:35,181 --> 00:08:37,225
gotten permission to
use the pool, I bet.

171
00:08:37,267 --> 00:08:38,309
[KAMINARI]
This works, and it could be

172
00:08:38,351 --> 00:08:40,311
the defining moment
of our lives.

173
00:08:40,353 --> 00:08:41,688
[MINETA]
Don't jinx us.

174
00:08:41,730 --> 00:08:43,898
I told you what I
heard the girls say.

175
00:08:43,940 --> 00:08:46,109
It was right after
the finals were over.

176
00:08:46,151 --> 00:08:47,736
Wait, so we're not
supposed to take any

177
00:08:47,777 --> 00:08:49,487
long trips over summer vacation?

178
00:08:49,529 --> 00:08:51,990
Yeah, apparently that's
what the school said.

179
00:08:52,032 --> 00:08:53,491
How unfortunate.

180
00:08:53,533 --> 00:08:55,076
I was supposed to
spend several weeks

181
00:08:55,118 --> 00:08:56,745
touring Venice with my parents.

182
00:08:56,786 --> 00:08:58,204
What is your life?

183
00:08:58,246 --> 00:09:01,833
Aw, and I just bought, like,
a bajillion new swimsuits.

184
00:09:01,875 --> 00:09:03,877
Well turns out,
that's what happens

185
00:09:03,918 --> 00:09:06,046
when your class is attacked
by the League of Villains.

186
00:09:06,087 --> 00:09:07,380
But I wanna <i>do</i> something!

187
00:09:07,422 --> 00:09:08,882
I don't wanna spend
my whole summer bored!

188
00:09:08,923 --> 00:09:10,050
‐‐That's so dumb!
‐‐[HAGAKURE] I've got it!

189
00:09:10,091 --> 00:09:11,509
Why don't we hang out
at the school pool

190
00:09:11,551 --> 00:09:13,428
over summer vacation, huh?

191
00:09:13,470 --> 00:09:14,637
Good idea.

192
00:09:14,679 --> 00:09:16,556
I bet we can talk the
teachers into letting us

193
00:09:16,598 --> 00:09:18,475
use it if we ask them nicely.

194
00:09:18,516 --> 00:09:20,977
Plus it'll be free,
so we'll save money.

195
00:09:21,019 --> 00:09:23,313
That's way better than
being cooped up in my room.

196
00:09:23,354 --> 00:09:24,355
Leave it to me.

197
00:09:24,397 --> 00:09:27,984
I'll start working on a
formal proposal right away.

198
00:09:28,026 --> 00:09:29,611
All the girls in
their swimsuits!

199
00:09:29,652 --> 00:09:32,197
[KAMINARI] It's our duty
to support our classmates.

200
00:09:32,238 --> 00:09:34,074
[MINETA] Just imagine how
voluptuous the girls

201
00:09:34,115 --> 00:09:36,409
are gonna be outside
of their uniforms.

202
00:09:36,451 --> 00:09:37,827
[MINETA, KAMINARI]
Faster, hurry up!

203
00:09:37,869 --> 00:09:42,749
Paradise is waiting on the
other side of this door!

204
00:09:42,791 --> 00:09:43,958
There you are, slowpokes.

205
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:45,210
[KAMINARI, MINETA yelp]

206
00:09:45,251 --> 00:09:46,252
[MINETA]
No, no, no.

207
00:09:46,294 --> 00:09:48,671
What the heck are
you guys doing here?

208
00:09:48,713 --> 00:09:50,882
Since we're doing endurance
training at the pool,

209
00:09:50,924 --> 00:09:53,218
I messaged everyone to see if
they wanted to come with us.

210
00:09:53,259 --> 00:09:54,344
You did what?

211
00:09:54,385 --> 00:09:56,096
Now all our plans are ruined.

212
00:09:56,137 --> 00:09:57,472
Don't lose hope yet.

213
00:09:57,514 --> 00:09:59,015
There will definitely
still be girls

214
00:09:59,057 --> 00:10:01,351
splashing around the water.

215
00:10:01,392 --> 00:10:03,853
[KAMINARI] I'll burn
the sight into my brain.

216
00:10:03,895 --> 00:10:06,147
[MINETA] I can't wait
to see those skimpy suits!

217
00:10:06,189 --> 00:10:07,774
Oh, hey. Hi, Mineta.

218
00:10:07,816 --> 00:10:09,234
I didn't know you guys
would be here.

219
00:10:09,275 --> 00:10:11,820
[KAMINARI] I can't believe
there's not a single bikini.

220
00:10:11,861 --> 00:10:12,987
Foiled again.

221
00:10:13,029 --> 00:10:15,281
You know, school suits
are still pretty hot.

222
00:10:15,323 --> 00:10:16,866
[KAMINARI]
Have some standards, dude.

223
00:10:16,908 --> 00:10:18,910
[TENYA]
Kaminari. Mineta. Nice work.

224
00:10:18,952 --> 00:10:20,829
I'm proud of you for
suggesting more training.

225
00:10:20,870 --> 00:10:24,165
You're an asset to our class.
Let me thank you.

226
00:10:24,207 --> 00:10:25,166
[BOTH whimper]

227
00:10:25,208 --> 00:10:26,835
[TENYA]
Now. Don't just sit there.

228
00:10:26,876 --> 00:10:29,003
It's time to come sweat with us.

229
00:10:29,045 --> 00:10:30,463
[TENYA laughs]

230
00:10:30,505 --> 00:10:32,799
‐‐[KAMINARI] You're choking me.
‐‐[MINETA] No, wait. Not cool!

231
00:10:32,841 --> 00:10:35,468
[KAMINARI, MINETA]
This wasn't the plan!

232
00:10:45,603 --> 00:10:49,149
[OCHACO]
Get ready for it! Serve!

233
00:10:49,190 --> 00:10:50,942
[ASHIDO]
Mine!

234
00:10:50,984 --> 00:10:52,569
[TSUYU]
Ribbit.

235
00:10:52,610 --> 00:10:54,154
[JIRO grunts]

236
00:10:54,195 --> 00:10:55,822
[HAGAKURE]
Got it!

237
00:10:55,864 --> 00:10:57,574
[YAOYOROZU]
Set!

238
00:10:57,615 --> 00:11:00,034
[TENYA] All right! Let's
take a 15‐minute breather.

239
00:11:00,076 --> 00:11:03,705
I brought these for everyone.
Please, drink up!

240
00:11:03,746 --> 00:11:04,664
[SATO]
Nice!

241
00:11:04,706 --> 00:11:05,874
[OJIRO]
Thanks a lot, Class Rep.

242
00:11:05,915 --> 00:11:08,126
[SERO]
This is just what I needed!

243
00:11:10,628 --> 00:11:12,922
[KAMINARI] Why do the girls
get to play around instead?

244
00:11:12,964 --> 00:11:14,382
[MINETA] They got permission
to use the pool,

245
00:11:14,424 --> 00:11:16,885
so they can goof off.
Can you believe it?

246
00:11:16,926 --> 00:11:18,052
You idiot.

247
00:11:18,094 --> 00:11:20,638
Why did you make our application
for endurance training.

248
00:11:20,680 --> 00:11:21,639
Sure, blame me,

249
00:11:21,681 --> 00:11:24,058
I didn't hear you
making any suggestions!

250
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:25,685
It looks like you've
been working out.

251
00:11:25,727 --> 00:11:27,353
I'm practically
living at the gym.

252
00:11:27,395 --> 00:11:29,230
It's been kinda nice, actually.

253
00:11:29,272 --> 00:11:31,232
[TOKOYAMI]
We must all remain focused.

254
00:11:31,274 --> 00:11:33,610
[panting]

255
00:11:33,651 --> 00:11:35,445
[TENYA]
Hey, Midoriya.

256
00:11:35,486 --> 00:11:37,113
It looks like you
could use a break.

257
00:11:37,155 --> 00:11:39,365
You're probably right, thanks.

258
00:11:43,453 --> 00:11:44,621
[IZUKU]
Something wrong?

259
00:11:44,662 --> 00:11:48,625
No. This is just
funny, that's all.

260
00:11:48,666 --> 00:11:50,210
At the entrance exams,

261
00:11:50,251 --> 00:11:52,337
I couldn't imagine the
two of us would get along,

262
00:11:52,378 --> 00:11:54,714
much less become
such good friends.

263
00:11:54,756 --> 00:11:56,382
I guess, if I'm being honest,

264
00:11:56,424 --> 00:11:59,052
I didn't think that
much of you back then.

265
00:11:59,093 --> 00:12:01,804
And yet. During the
practical exam...

266
00:12:04,057 --> 00:12:06,684
[OCHACO grunting]

267
00:12:06,726 --> 00:12:07,936
[IZUKU grunts]

268
00:12:09,562 --> 00:12:13,233
[IZUKU]
Smash!

269
00:12:16,110 --> 00:12:18,696
You did put Uraraka
ahead of yourself.

270
00:12:18,738 --> 00:12:22,242
Even though saving her
meant you might not pass.

271
00:12:22,283 --> 00:12:24,118
[ALL MIGHT] How could a
hero course reject someone

272
00:12:24,160 --> 00:12:25,828
who is committed
to saving others,

273
00:12:25,870 --> 00:12:28,831
no matter the
consequences to himself?

274
00:12:28,873 --> 00:12:31,918
After all, that is
what makes a hero.

275
00:12:31,960 --> 00:12:36,256
Welcome, Izuku.

276
00:12:36,297 --> 00:12:37,465
You have made it.

277
00:12:37,507 --> 00:12:41,010
You're now part of
the hero academia.

278
00:12:41,052 --> 00:12:42,887
I was so happy.

279
00:12:42,929 --> 00:12:44,722
It had always been a
dream of mine to attend

280
00:12:44,764 --> 00:12:46,474
All Might's alma mater someday.

281
00:12:46,516 --> 00:12:48,768
Even though I knew
it was a long shot.

282
00:12:48,810 --> 00:12:51,521
And then, when Mr. Aizawa
said the person

283
00:12:51,562 --> 00:12:54,148
in last place for the fitness
test would be expelled,

284
00:12:54,190 --> 00:12:56,651
I was sure I'd be going home.

285
00:12:56,693 --> 00:12:58,820
You may have thought that,
but you never gave up.

286
00:12:58,861 --> 00:12:59,696
Oh.

287
00:12:59,737 --> 00:13:01,447
Not during combat
training, either.

288
00:13:01,489 --> 00:13:04,158
[IZUKU]
Detroit...

289
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:07,412
[yelling]

290
00:13:07,453 --> 00:13:11,207
[IZUKU]
...Smash!

291
00:13:13,793 --> 00:13:16,671
[TENYA gasps]
What's happening?

292
00:13:16,713 --> 00:13:21,342
Improvised special move,
the Comet Home Run!

293
00:13:23,177 --> 00:13:24,429
[TENYA]
In the name of villainy,

294
00:13:24,470 --> 00:13:26,723
I demand that you stop this!

295
00:13:28,349 --> 00:13:29,434
I've got it!

296
00:13:29,475 --> 00:13:30,727
[TENYA gasps]

297
00:13:30,768 --> 00:13:35,523
This is the only way
I had any chance at winning.

298
00:13:35,565 --> 00:13:36,774
[TENYA]
You weren't perfect.

299
00:13:36,816 --> 00:13:38,943
Indeed, your methods
were reckless.

300
00:13:38,985 --> 00:13:40,695
But I could feel the
tenacity and drive

301
00:13:40,737 --> 00:13:42,905
you brought to each test.

302
00:13:42,947 --> 00:13:44,741
I believe that's the
reason Bakugo and I

303
00:13:44,782 --> 00:13:46,868
lost to you in our
training round.

304
00:13:46,909 --> 00:13:48,411
Thanks, Iida.

305
00:13:49,454 --> 00:13:51,205
But I'm only here
because so many people

306
00:13:51,247 --> 00:13:52,457
have helped me get here.

307
00:13:52,498 --> 00:13:53,708
And that's why

308
00:13:53,750 --> 00:13:55,168
I'll work even
harder from now on!

309
00:13:55,209 --> 00:13:56,919
[KATSUKI]
You'd better!

310
00:13:56,961 --> 00:13:58,713
The next time I beat you,

311
00:13:58,755 --> 00:14:01,591
I want you to be at your
strongest, you damn nerd.

312
00:14:01,632 --> 00:14:03,051
[IZUKU yelps]
Kacchan!

313
00:14:03,092 --> 00:14:04,135
Hey, I got your message.

314
00:14:04,177 --> 00:14:04,969
Sorry I'm late.

315
00:14:05,011 --> 00:14:07,472
Took a while to convince
Bakugo to come out.

316
00:14:07,513 --> 00:14:09,182
[IZUKU]
That's not very surprising.

317
00:14:09,223 --> 00:14:11,351
[KATSUKI]
So, Deku.

318
00:14:11,392 --> 00:14:14,604
You wanna settle who's the best
between us right now? Huh?

319
00:14:14,645 --> 00:14:15,938
No. That's not it.

320
00:14:15,980 --> 00:14:17,231
Actually, you know what?

321
00:14:17,273 --> 00:14:18,941
We could make this
training a contest.

322
00:14:18,983 --> 00:14:19,692
Huh?

323
00:14:19,734 --> 00:14:20,568
[TENYA]
Hey, everyone!

324
00:14:20,610 --> 00:14:22,111
I propose that we see
which of the boys

325
00:14:22,153 --> 00:14:23,988
can swim 50 meters the fastest.

326
00:14:24,030 --> 00:14:24,906
A friendly race.

327
00:14:24,947 --> 00:14:26,032
Yeah!

328
00:14:26,074 --> 00:14:27,241
That sounds fun.

329
00:14:27,283 --> 00:14:28,493
Let's do it!

330
00:14:28,534 --> 00:14:29,577
[YAOYOROZU]
Iida!

331
00:14:29,619 --> 00:14:31,496
Why don't you let us
help you out with this?

332
00:14:31,537 --> 00:14:32,372
Yes, please.

333
00:14:32,413 --> 00:14:34,791
And, Quirks. Can we use them?

334
00:14:34,832 --> 00:14:36,000
[TENYA] We're at school,
so there shouldn't

335
00:14:36,042 --> 00:14:39,045
be a problem with that. However!
You cannot cause damage

336
00:14:39,087 --> 00:14:41,756
to your classmates
or the building.

337
00:14:41,798 --> 00:14:44,300
I'm gonna annihilate you, Deku.

338
00:14:45,593 --> 00:14:49,013
And you, too, Icy Hot.
You bastard!

339
00:14:54,477 --> 00:14:56,896
All right, now, everyone,
on your marks!

340
00:14:56,938 --> 00:14:58,689
Get set!

341
00:14:58,731 --> 00:15:00,108
[whistle blows]

342
00:15:00,149 --> 00:15:03,778
[KATSUKI]
Burst Speed Turbo!

343
00:15:03,820 --> 00:15:05,488
How was that, you sidekicks?

344
00:15:05,530 --> 00:15:06,572
What do you think you're doing?

345
00:15:06,614 --> 00:15:08,074
You didn't even touch the water!

346
00:15:08,116 --> 00:15:10,993
It's called freestyle swimming!

347
00:15:11,035 --> 00:15:13,955
[YAOYOROZU]
Everyone on your marks. Get set!

348
00:15:13,996 --> 00:15:15,039
[whistle blows]

349
00:15:16,958 --> 00:15:18,251
[AOYAMA]
Bonjour!

350
00:15:19,252 --> 00:15:20,253
[SERO grunts]

351
00:15:23,881 --> 00:15:26,384
[BOTH]
You're supposed to be swimming!

352
00:15:26,426 --> 00:15:30,388
[YAOYOROZU] Last group,
on your marks. Get set!

353
00:15:30,430 --> 00:15:31,431
[whistle blows]

354
00:15:34,308 --> 00:15:36,018
[KAMINARI]
You, too, Iida?

355
00:15:36,060 --> 00:15:39,480
[IZUKU]
One for All, Full Cowling!

356
00:15:53,286 --> 00:15:54,287
[gasps]

357
00:15:54,328 --> 00:15:55,413
[STUDENTS cheer]

358
00:15:55,455 --> 00:15:56,914
Nice one, Midoriya!

359
00:15:56,956 --> 00:15:58,624
Iida, was so close!

360
00:15:58,666 --> 00:16:00,209
You beat me. Good work.

361
00:16:00,251 --> 00:16:02,837
[IZUKU] You were amazing
out there, too, Iida!

362
00:16:02,879 --> 00:16:04,714
Midoriya...

363
00:16:04,755 --> 00:16:06,883
So if you're connected
to the number‐one hero,

364
00:16:06,924 --> 00:16:08,759
All Might, in some way,

365
00:16:08,801 --> 00:16:10,428
that would mean...

366
00:16:10,470 --> 00:16:13,806
...that I have even more
reason to beat you.

367
00:16:13,848 --> 00:16:14,849
You see,

368
00:16:14,891 --> 00:16:17,768
I'm going to show my old man
that I reject his power,

369
00:16:17,810 --> 00:16:21,189
and I can take first place
without using it.

370
00:16:21,230 --> 00:16:24,192
[IZUKU] You think you can win
with half your strength?

371
00:16:24,233 --> 00:16:26,152
Look at me, Todoroki.

372
00:16:26,194 --> 00:16:30,198
You haven't managed to put
a single scratch on me yet.

373
00:16:30,239 --> 00:16:32,825
So come at me
with all you've got!

374
00:16:34,368 --> 00:16:37,622
It's yours! Your Quirk, not his!

375
00:16:41,417 --> 00:16:43,211
I want it, too.

376
00:16:43,252 --> 00:16:45,129
I'll be a hero!

377
00:16:52,678 --> 00:16:55,139
[TENYA] You must be
the Hero Killer, Stain!

378
00:16:57,266 --> 00:16:59,352
[TENYA] I am the brother
of an incredible hero

379
00:16:59,393 --> 00:17:01,479
who you attacked.

380
00:17:01,521 --> 00:17:05,107
He's the best older brother
that anyone could hope for.

381
00:17:05,149 --> 00:17:06,817
I have come to stop you,

382
00:17:06,859 --> 00:17:09,070
because he can't anymore.

383
00:17:12,114 --> 00:17:12,990
[grunts]

384
00:17:13,032 --> 00:17:14,158
You aren't heroes.

385
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:16,619
You have no right
to be called that.

386
00:17:16,661 --> 00:17:19,247
Both of you are
nothing but fakes.

387
00:17:19,288 --> 00:17:21,123
[IZUKU]
Smash!

388
00:17:23,376 --> 00:17:27,046
Don't you worry, Iida.
I'm gonna save you.

389
00:17:27,088 --> 00:17:30,466
I was almost too late
to stop this guy.

390
00:17:30,508 --> 00:17:32,593
We can protect them!

391
00:17:32,635 --> 00:17:34,011
Just stop it.

392
00:17:34,053 --> 00:17:36,764
Why are you... doing this?

393
00:17:36,806 --> 00:17:39,058
His fight is with me!

394
00:17:39,100 --> 00:17:42,770
I inherited my brother's name.

395
00:17:42,812 --> 00:17:43,980
You have to run.

396
00:17:44,021 --> 00:17:45,022
[TODOROKI gasps]

397
00:17:45,064 --> 00:17:47,900
I can't... watch this.

398
00:17:49,151 --> 00:17:50,820
You wanna make
your brother proud?

399
00:17:50,861 --> 00:17:51,779
[gasps]

400
00:17:51,821 --> 00:17:54,699
Become the hero
he wanted you to be!

401
00:17:56,325 --> 00:17:57,577
[TENYA]
Todoroki.

402
00:17:57,618 --> 00:18:02,707
I vow once more to become
a hero like my older brother.

403
00:18:02,748 --> 00:18:04,250
[TODOROKI]
I will become a hero,

404
00:18:04,292 --> 00:18:06,294
but the kind that <i>I</i> wanna be.

405
00:18:06,335 --> 00:18:08,337
[IZUKU]
I swear I'll become a hero.

406
00:18:08,379 --> 00:18:10,881
A great one, like All Might.

407
00:18:10,923 --> 00:18:13,217
Who saves people with a smile.

408
00:18:15,261 --> 00:18:16,512
[TSUKAUCHI]
UA High School was attacked

409
00:18:16,554 --> 00:18:19,890
by the League of Villains during
a rescue training session.

410
00:18:19,932 --> 00:18:23,894
It would come to be referred
to as the USJ Incident.

411
00:18:23,936 --> 00:18:26,314
Then there were the attacks
by the Hero Killer Stain

412
00:18:26,355 --> 00:18:28,482
and the League of
Villains in Hosu City,

413
00:18:28,524 --> 00:18:31,068
in what became known
as the Hosu Incident.

414
00:18:31,110 --> 00:18:34,113
And just a few days ago,
Tomura Shigaraki,

415
00:18:34,155 --> 00:18:36,240
thought to be the leader
of the League of Villains,

416
00:18:36,282 --> 00:18:37,908
cornered Izuku Midoriya,

417
00:18:37,950 --> 00:18:41,495
a student in the hero
course at UA High.

418
00:18:41,537 --> 00:18:43,122
As far as we can tell,

419
00:18:43,164 --> 00:18:45,166
the League of Villains
hasn't made a move since.

420
00:18:45,207 --> 00:18:46,167
That's true.

421
00:18:46,208 --> 00:18:47,835
But I'm sure they're
hiding in the shadows,

422
00:18:47,877 --> 00:18:49,503
waiting to strike again.

423
00:18:49,545 --> 00:18:51,047
Likely, yes.

424
00:18:51,088 --> 00:18:53,549
The police are currently
working alongside heroes

425
00:18:53,591 --> 00:18:56,510
to gather as much information
about the group as possible.

426
00:18:56,552 --> 00:18:59,013
When we do find out
where they've been hiding,

427
00:18:59,055 --> 00:19:01,766
we'll need you, All Might.

428
00:19:01,807 --> 00:19:05,269
I won't disappoint
you, Tsukauchi.

429
00:19:05,311 --> 00:19:07,229
[TENYA]
It's time for the final race.

430
00:19:07,271 --> 00:19:09,273
Bakugo. Todoroki. Midoriya.

431
00:19:09,315 --> 00:19:10,358
As the winners of each heat,

432
00:19:10,399 --> 00:19:12,443
you'll fight for
first place. Understand?

433
00:19:12,485 --> 00:19:14,070
‐‐[IZUKU] Got it.
‐‐[TODOROKI] Yes.

434
00:19:14,111 --> 00:19:16,489
Listen up, Scarface.

435
00:19:16,530 --> 00:19:19,909
Don't you dare hold back like
you did at the sports festival.

436
00:19:19,950 --> 00:19:21,786
Bring everything you've got!

437
00:19:21,827 --> 00:19:23,204
I will.

438
00:19:23,245 --> 00:19:25,331
You, too. Fight to win.

439
00:19:25,373 --> 00:19:28,334
Yeah! I will. I promise.

440
00:19:28,376 --> 00:19:30,378
[TENYA] Then the 50‐meter
freestyle final race

441
00:19:30,419 --> 00:19:31,921
will now begin!

442
00:19:31,962 --> 00:19:33,047
Blow 'em away, Bakugo!

443
00:19:33,089 --> 00:19:34,590
Don't kill the other swimmers!

444
00:19:34,632 --> 00:19:36,050
You got this, Todoroki!

445
00:19:36,092 --> 00:19:37,551
You can do it, Deku!

446
00:19:37,593 --> 00:19:39,220
Do your best, everyone!

447
00:19:39,261 --> 00:19:40,596
Now, on your marks.

448
00:19:41,681 --> 00:19:44,308
[KATSUKI] A single blast
is all it'll take.

449
00:19:44,350 --> 00:19:46,185
[TODOROKI]
I'll slide past them.

450
00:19:46,227 --> 00:19:49,313
[IZUKU]
I can win this with One For All.

451
00:19:49,355 --> 00:19:50,439
[TENYA]
Get set!

452
00:19:50,481 --> 00:19:51,691
[whistle blows]

453
00:19:51,732 --> 00:19:53,651
[ALL yelp]

454
00:19:53,693 --> 00:19:54,777
What happened?

455
00:19:54,819 --> 00:19:56,696
Why aren't they
using their Quirks?

456
00:19:56,737 --> 00:19:58,406
[AIZAWA]
It's 5 pm.

457
00:19:58,447 --> 00:20:01,409
Your authorized pool time
is officially over.

458
00:20:01,450 --> 00:20:02,785
Hurry up and go home.

459
00:20:02,827 --> 00:20:04,036
[KAMINARI]
Come on, just one second!

460
00:20:04,078 --> 00:20:06,664
[SERO] We were finally
getting to the good part!

461
00:20:06,706 --> 00:20:08,457
Are you questioning me?

462
00:20:08,499 --> 00:20:11,711
[STUDENTS]
Not at all, Mr. Aizawa!

463
00:20:11,752 --> 00:20:12,545
[KATSUKI]
Dammit!

464
00:20:12,586 --> 00:20:14,547
I can't believe he stopped
the race like that.

465
00:20:14,588 --> 00:20:17,633
Yeah, I know how you feel,
but cool your blasters, man.

466
00:20:17,675 --> 00:20:19,719
Those two aren't just
your opponents, you know.

467
00:20:19,760 --> 00:20:20,678
They're our friends.

468
00:20:20,720 --> 00:20:22,430
Shut up!

469
00:20:22,471 --> 00:20:24,724
I don't care if they're
my classmates or not.

470
00:20:24,765 --> 00:20:27,435
I won't let them
get ahead of me.

471
00:20:27,476 --> 00:20:30,020
Isn't that what it means
to be number one?

472
00:20:30,062 --> 00:20:32,773
To be the best, I'll have to
be stronger than All Might.

473
00:20:32,815 --> 00:20:34,817
It's only a matter of time.

474
00:20:40,239 --> 00:20:42,992
[ALL MIGHT] You have ten months
until the UA Entrance exam.

475
00:20:43,033 --> 00:20:45,453
You must build up your
body in that time.

476
00:20:48,122 --> 00:20:50,166
[ALL MIGHT]
Young Midoriya?

477
00:20:50,207 --> 00:20:53,544
[IZUKU] All Might!
What are you doing here?

478
00:20:53,586 --> 00:20:55,796
[ALL MIGHT]
I could ask you the same.

479
00:20:55,838 --> 00:20:57,757
[IZUKU]
I am here...

480
00:20:57,798 --> 00:21:01,552
[ALL MIGHT] Young man.
You, too, can become a hero.

481
00:21:01,594 --> 00:21:02,803
The truth is,

482
00:21:02,845 --> 00:21:05,389
there's nothing natural
about my Quirk.

483
00:21:05,431 --> 00:21:06,974
I wasn't born with this power,

484
00:21:07,016 --> 00:21:09,101
it's a sacred torch
that was passed on to me

485
00:21:09,143 --> 00:21:10,561
from someone else.

486
00:21:10,603 --> 00:21:12,855
I can transfer
my Quirk to another.

487
00:21:12,897 --> 00:21:16,108
And that's only one facet
of my secret abilities.

488
00:21:16,150 --> 00:21:21,197
The true name of my
power is One For All.

489
00:21:21,238 --> 00:21:22,448
You're next, kid.

490
00:21:22,490 --> 00:21:25,451
You are my worthy successor.

491
00:21:25,493 --> 00:21:29,371
...because this is where
my journey began.

492
00:21:32,124 --> 00:21:33,584
[ALL MIGHT]
Young Midoriya,

493
00:21:33,626 --> 00:21:35,878
the summer training
camp will be tough.

494
00:21:35,920 --> 00:21:37,296
Try your hardest.

495
00:21:37,338 --> 00:21:38,464
[IZUKU]
I will!

496
00:23:08,721 --> 00:23:11,557
[VLAD] So the location of
the training camp has moved?

497
00:23:11,599 --> 00:23:12,391
[AIZAWA]
Yes.

